description:
Contents

  • Dragon Ball Super Chapter 8
The truth about Stargirl's father is revealed as the Bombshells discover a traitor in their midst.
name: Allies Part 9 of 9

description:
Secret Origins

In this issue Will finds out the terrible history of Antispire. The rise and fall of a kingdom and its champions. Most bizarre of all, Will finds out his connection to this world goes far deeper than he could have ever imagined...
name: Secret Origins

description: Bernard, Dean, and Professor Thorston unravel mysteries within mysteries past the gates of Midlothian Seafood. Meanwhile Teddy and Johannes evade zombies and encounter big friendly dinos.

2039

The Detective delves deeper into the mystery in New Amsterdam; bodies begin to mount as more layers are discovered.
name: Vol. 2

description: Tenor sax man Jimmy Watts and his piano playing friend Slim Watkins make the transition from swing-era music students to professional jazz musicians of the be-bop era. Witness the founding of their cool new combo Bughouse, as the spectre of an alluring drug known as “bug juice” creeps into the scene, in cartoonist Steve Lafler's insect-noir classic.

Cold War

Crimson and Caress are back home at Groom Lake and it isn't long before old grudges rear their ugly head. The team also go against a cold war era soldier that is out of his own time. Come meet General Russia!
name: Cold War

description:
Exorcists

Connor tries to unravel the mysteries surrounding what his dark power is. Meanwhile the "other" him keeps taking sinners souls and the events are becoming more and more frequent. He has caught the eye of an organization, who are they and what do they want with Connor?
name: Exorcists

description:
The Musical

Singing! Dancing! Hear Bob sing about his life and what drives him to do the things he does. (And... In the process, find out why musicals don't work in comic book form.) --A real tear jerker!
name: The Musical

description: Contains more experimental black and white comics, including "How the Raven and the Loon Got Their Colors" based on a Yup'ik folktale.

We're talking cute, but with a Calvin and Hobbes-ian twist." --Mike Wilson, features editor, St. Petersburg Times In the spirit of Snoopy and Charlie Brown, or Calvin and Hobbes, please welcome Sophie and Doug. Dog Eat Doug is the cartooning creation of Brian Anderson that follows the daily exploits of Sophie, a cheese-loving chocolate Lab with a nose for the nuances of sarcasm and irony, and baby Doug, a healthy, happy newborn with no concept of jealousy and a limitless curiosity. Together, this dynamic duo adjusts to sharing the spotlight, the toys, and the affections of Mom and Dad, while exploring nature and its majesty, the couch and its cushions, and the cookie jar and its contents.
name: It Came from the Diaper Pail

description:
Dreams

A wild bear dreams in color as the robotic Duke absorbs human dreams for energy on a distant planet with beastly spirits killing humans. Can the bear save the fight off Duke and catch his dream of finding the lost princess?
name: Dreams

description:
It's a time of love and regret in Echo Gear.

"When nothing around us mattered.

And all was pure and tranquil."

The Emotional Lives of Engineers - Part 2

Shae's world is turned upside down. After suddenly experiencing a bout of unconsciousness during a critical mission, she wakes to learn things about herself that confound her imagination. Not only does she not know who she is, she doesn't even know what she is. Run away with Shae in search of her mysterious "family" as Albertron gets left behind to agonize in worry and remorse, his penance for the secrets he's kept from Shae from the beginning.
name: The Emotional Lives of Engineers Part 2

description:
Volume 3: Creature Compendium

Role-Players, not Role Models.

The continuing adventures of Fili (a Fighter), and Noli (a Wizard), in high fantasy hubris and idiocy.

This collection of comic strips first appeared online at favouritecrayon.co.uk, and is packed full of #MMO #RPG #metahumour.
name: Volume 3: Creature Compendium

volume.name: Experience the Magic of the Legend!

description:
Suitcase Full of Eyeballs

Hex has a lot on her mind, not the least of which is one of the biggest Slicks in her career, it's the job that just might push her over the edge and out of the business. This issue lands us in the glass clad towers of Districit 04, Palomar's Silicon Alley - home to some of the biggest corporations in the world and the most expensive realestate in the city. It is one year before the District 8 bombing when Hex Spencer begins her Gatecrashing career.
name: Suitcase Full of Eyeballs

description: The third chapter of The Happiness Agent continues Lorelai's hunt, this time through the memories of the agent who tried to alter her thoughts. But will his background give her more answers or more problems?
name: Chapter Three

description:
It's the indie comic crossover you never knew you wanted!

The Prince of Darkness and The Mahatma, those mismatched roommates from "The Devil and Mr. Gandhi" find their way to the bar where mythical icons go to unwind - Holidaze!

Why does Gandhi find The Devil taking a part-time bartender job at Holidaze?

What is The Devil really up to with his Christmas wish for Santa?

Why are the Holidaze gang plagued by the Prince of Darkness' pranks?

And will karma finally catch up to Devil for orchestrating this comic crossover in the first place?!

Questions you never had finally get answered as Holidaze Meets The Devil and Mr. Gandhi!

volume.name: Holidaze Meets the Devil & Mr. Gandhi

description: We must remember that respect is earned and not just given away. What secrets lay in this new place the drifter has found? How are things going to play out now that he has been accepted into the group?

The Day They Arrived, Part 2

The story unfolds as aliens establish a foothold in a small rural town. Two teens, the only witnesses of the arrival of the aliens, are lost, transported by a malfunctioning alien device to an unknown location. As they struggle to find their way home, what will become of the town of Percyville?
name: The Day They Arrived, Part 2

volume.name: Keith C Bradbury's The Peregrin Chronicles

description:
Corruption

When the police bot initiative backfires, The Lightspeed Enforcers are left with the task of bringing the robots down.
name: Corruption

description:
One Previous Owner

Lou relates the tale of how he became the owner and captain of the starship 'Raging Hormone'. A tale of beer, honour, and space pirates...
name: One Previous Owner

description:
A Rusty Knife is twice as Deadly

Lower East Side Story #5 shows tensions building to the breaking point: a previously unknown disease is now running rampant, and the outlook is not good. The neighborhood sees the first after shocks of crack cocaine taking hold of its first victims, and Sponge may survive from Red's brutal attack.

This is the next chapter of Pete Friedrich's remarkable tale taking place in New York in the 1980s, a city at the brink of bankruptcy and total collapse.

This special double issue features 44 pages of art plus a color cover, with colors by Michael Neno.

Conniption Fit!!!

Electrolyte sits trapped in a sinking ship in water nostrils-high and rising while Conniption has kidnapped Sparker.
name: Conniption Fit!!!

volume.name: The Misadventures of Electrolyte and The Justice Purveyors

description:
The Ophydian Conspiracy

The Ophydians are among us. Intelligent reptiles with one objective in their cold-blooded hearts: to enslave the human race. They control our politicians, our corporate executives and our society. They're responsible for political corruption the War On Terror and economic collapse ... at least according to Victor Vega, monster hunter.
name: The Ophydian Conspiracy

description:
Give Up the Ghost

Peter Hadley has a rough life, and the only adult who seems to notice is the school nurse. But things get harder when a strange woman appears and Peter begins to see ghosts.
name: Give Up the Ghost

description:
Master of Puppets

On the run from Baker and his pack, Bastion and the team head towards Beau Fort for safety. Or so they think.
name: Master of Puppets

description:
Working Class Hero

One year after learning Martial Arts from Master Pembo, it's time for the young Karaoke Singer turned Hero to go out onto the streets of Port Sanford and find a job.
name: Working Class Hero

description:
After saving his people and his empire from his tyrannical litter-mate, Sarq'Dar, Emperor Oby'Dar sits upon the throne of the Grand Parliament of the Continuum watching as the days of heroics now pale in to the return of the politics of a free society.

As the empire debates about a new unseen threat, Oby'Dar must act to save all he struggled to free...

Red, having harrowed her encounter with Gigglehorn and his flesh golem Churlish Joe, reaches the shores of an ocean made of churning bone. On her attempt to cross she finds the bones make for a perilous perambulate. The Wolfe sits on the front steps of Grandmother's house and waits.
name: The Bone Tide

description:
Sensation

Michael returns to the city and shocks the world as he shares his messianic gifts with the people. Adam shares a deeply held secret with Noa.
name: Sensation

description:
Rescue in Koman

Rob partners with a rival private security firm to rescue a downed U.S. air force pilot who is being held hostage in the Middle East.
name: Rescue in Koman

description:
Best game ever. Probably...

The 5th issue of the Roleplayers comic series!

This is it. The final showdown between the Roleplayers and Lance.

Pitting their wits and luck against one another, a historic battle is set in motion as Cassandra the cleric, sylvia the druid, Barbie the barbarian and gwen the giant spider mount their final assault against Abidah the warlock and her demonic horde.

Will the heroines prevail or will the warlock succeed in her evil schemes?

Read on as the roleplayers settle their dispute roleplay style.

Whatever happens on the table, stays ermm... on the table?

Find out what happens in Roleplayers #5!

The Wizard

Raymond encounters a grouchy scientist named Wally Ding who happens to be evolving into a fish. Raymond tries to persuade Wally to remain among humans by taking him to a terrible art exhibit.
name: The Wizard

description:
Empty Canvas

The twenty-third issue of Strip For Me. There are scars and art and tragedy, just like always, as a model goes to work with an artist who may have been involved with her twin sister.
name: Empty Canvas

description:
Holly Hommy

A future-tech, dystopian swamp world adventure book, with super powers, gangsters, ninjas, action, comedy and maybe a robot or two.
name: Holly Hommy

description: The entire Terminus army is united against a new threat to the city.

Clash of the Titans

Violence abounds as the knockout dark historical fantasy series of the Irish War for Independence continues. In this action-packed double issue Michael Collins meets Crowley for the first time and relays the underpinnings of the revolution.
name: Clash of the Titans

description:
Hunter's Moon Pt. 3

The Wolfen have found their prey and Virgin, Hania, and Crimson Mask may not live through the night to tell the tale.
name: Hunter's Moon Pt. 3

description:
The End is Not Yet

While battling supernatural forces The Briathos is mortally wounded. At death's door he reflects on his life as we discover his origin.
name: The End is Not Yet

description:
CAPTAIN FROG and the STAR BABE...The COMIC!

Aw Yeah Comics Presents Scoot McMahon's Captain Frog and the Star Babe:

Adventure and embarrassment!

That's been the life of Captain Frog since The Star Babe has joined the crew of the starship Lilypad.

Will the Star Babe's quest for excitement doom the starship before Captain Frog has a chance to ask her out??

Story and art by cartoonist Scoot McMahon

volume.name: Captain Frog and The Star Babe

description:
Damages

Who can you really trust? We live in a world where politicians spin intricate webs of lies as a part of their job description. But nobody is prepared for what happens when those lies are more dangerous than anyone could have imagined.

Carmen, in the grips of grief for her boyfriend, discovers she is hunted by the Government and now must find out why.
name: Damages

description:
Book III, Chapter I

Moving to Grey Oaks was an opportunity for the Barrot family to start again. A chance to escape the darkness that had almost consumed them. A chance to forget would could have been and look forward to the future. But in the shadows, something was watching, something that had decided they were special.

And so, the darkness came to town.

Shadows moving through the night, branding human livestock with strangely shaped symbols in final preparation for the Great Black Flood that would come to eat the world.
name: Chapter 1

description:
The Decision

In an apocalyptic future, one Russian military leader struggles to hold the city of Moscow together after a deadly virus spreads throughout the world, only to years later discover that his adopted daughter has joined the resistance.
name: The Decision

description:
Dark Sonata - A 70-page Horror Graphic Novel

From the moment he receives an unexpected phone call, everything that is happening to Adam is a complete nightmare. He gets involved in a series of strange and bizarre events while searching for his old love - a girl named Annabel.

The weird journey he suddenly fell into, eventually leads him to an obscure old house where reality and imagination are strongly crossed and the story is heading for creepy culmination. Adam realizes that everything is possible, but also that nothing is like it seems...

Manga Contents

  • Shurayuki-hime

A sci-fi graphic novel with stunning cinematic quality and an intriguing story inspired by classic sci-fi horror films of Ridley Scott. The story takes place in the post-apocalyptic world of the After Reset setting.

Can We Skip to the Part of the Conversation Where I Get My Way? compiles the first two years of Finn and Charlie are Hitched, a webcomic telling the story of a married gay couple, their friends, and their adventures in domesticity.
name: Can We Skip to the Part of the Conversation Where I Get My Way?

description: Kedzie is an android programmed to watch over humanity while it sleeps. This is the start of the worst day of her life.

Collects Issues 1-5.

Life is a cruel, twisted joke. Kane Kage knows this all too well. Raised by a single, workaholic father, Kage knew neglect at a very young age. But despite this, he still grew up idolizing him. Tragically everything changes when his father, the one clean lawyer in town, chooses to represent a known criminal. Feeling betrayed, Kage descends down a path of rebellion and destruction. It is after his father's noble end that Kage once again sets himself on the right path. Driven by guilt and rage, he seeks the means to execute justice, finally receiving it after his own death, when he returns from hell. Get ready for a story of rage, redemption, and revenge, as Kane battles not just his own demons, but those that walk the earth, seeking to inflict ruin upon mankind.

College is an important part of life. It's also really stupid if you actually think about it.

Witness as the first stone of a university is laid! Watch the predictions of a made-up pre-hispanic cult! Learn how to cut what might possibly be a drug reference that will DEFINITELY not tell you exactly where this story takes place.

And yes, this is entirely based on how awful my college experience was...

In the 1950s, the U.S. Navy encountered and destroyed a gigantic octopus that attacked shipping and wreaked havoc on the west coast of the United States. American forces killed the creature and ended the threat once and for all. Or so they thought. They were wrong. Now, another monster is rising in the warm blue waters surrounding Taru Taru, a speck of land far out in the Pacific. And this time it's worse than anyone ever imagined.
name: Chapter One

volume.name: It Came From Beneath The Sea... Again!

description: Based on his short film of the same name. A charming but melancholy story about a lonely lady who can hear ghosts and longs for a friend.

Preview Issue

An uncharted island, magical beasts, tattooed natives, and a young woman who washed up on the shore. Unless June wants to live the rest of her life without a shower and cell service, she needs to find her way back home.

volume.name: The Lost Island of the Na-Rune-Tok

description: Uki Ogasawara (Black Sun) was the special guest for 2012's Yaoicon. It was her first con attendance located in a hotel, and DMP's first year as the event's hosts. So, what did she think and how did it all go? Come on and find out!

The dawn of bio-engineering changed the criminal landscape for the worse. Genetic modification and bio-organic weapons have revolutionized the black markets and gave rise to a new kind of criminal: The Geneticist. These "doctors" play god with the lives of millions of people. No longer are gangs limited by their own poor abilities or intellect. If they can pay, they get equipped with the latest in genetic and cybernetic advancements.

This process is of course highly illegal, but since when has that ever stopped criminals from doing what they do? They are criminals after all. Genetically enhanced criminals overpower the police already, but their growing numbers make matters worse than they already are. Of course, corrupt businessmen and politicians have a great interest in augmented enforcers the police can not stop. There is a lot of profit to be made with such people.

What these dark times need are heroes that are not afraid to fight back, that go to the ends of the earth to save us. But how desperate must a man be if he risked losing it all to fight back? Only if you have already lost everything, you have nothing left to lose. Nightfighter is one such man. His life completely destroyed by the accident that gave him his powers, he now fights to stop those who use their powers to oppress the weak.
name: Vol. 1
